WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.500
The fact that over 50%, as far as we can tell,
of gray whale populations have been lost.

00:00:07.500 --> 00:00:09.500
Like people don't really know that.

00:00:09.500 --> 00:00:20.000
We basically used to have a thriving business
from December through April for gray whales.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:22.000
I no longer have much business for them.

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:28.000
Eventually, their drop is going to bottom out,
and then there will be a balance.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:31.000
I think awareness is a big part of it.

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:33.000
This isn't really the best time politically.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:41.000
But these whales, by the law of the Endangered Species Act,
should go back onto the endangered species list.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:48.000
But they won't unless we act like,
okay, if we care about these individual whales,

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:54.000
then we'll start caring about the broader picture
of the ocean and the health of our oceans.